# CalvyBots Dashboard — Cursor Project Rules

## Project identity

Product name: **Launchpad** (CalvyBots personal quick-access dashboard).
Repo root: `/workspace` (Cursor Cloud) / `n:/web_app` (host).
Stack: **static-first** — HTML5 + Alpine.js CDN + Tailwind Play CDN + vanilla ES modules. No build step, no bundler, no TypeScript compilation.

---

## Non-negotiable constraints

- **Never run Python scripts.** No `python`, `python3`, or `py` invocations. Avoid generating Python testing scripts.
- **No automated test frameworks or test harnesses** unless the client explicitly requests them.
- **No README files** unless explicitly requested.
- **No bundlers, transpilers, or build steps** — ever. CDN-only dependencies.
- **No `npm install`, `yarn`, or `pnpm`** for the main app. The `api/` service has its own package management but lives outside the delivered static tree.
- **Never create standalone test scripts or unit test files** as part of feature work.

---

## Team structure and subagent roles

Five Cursor agent personas are defined under `.cursor/agents/`. Respect these roles:

| Agent | When to invoke |
|-------|---------------|
| `team-lead` | Sequencing work, delegation, authoring/updating `team/` docs, tightening acceptance criteria |
| `frontend-senior-dev` | UI, widgets, `js/store.js`, `js/app.js`, `css/style.css`, `index.html`, edit mode, PWA frontend assets |
| `backend-senior-dev` | `nginx-site.conf`, `sw.js`, MIME types, caching, security headers, `/api/` coexistence |
| `qa-engineer` | Static review, usability checklists, PWA sign-off, `team/qa-*.md` and `tests/` artifacts |
| `senior-cleanup-engineer` | **Client-only.** Do NOT invoke autonomously or proactively. Only when client personally requests by name. |

**Model policy (all agents):** Default to **Codex 3.5 Spark preview** (`gpt-5.3-codex-spark-preview`). Escalate through Team Lead only; never self-select Opus without explicit client confirmation.

---

## Architecture rules

### Static-first contract
- All deliverables are **static files** served by nginx with no build step.
- Entry point: `index.html` (Alpine.js `x-data="launchpad"` root).
- Styles: Tailwind via **Play CDN** + `css/style.css` custom tokens.
- Logic: vanilla ES modules in `js/` — `app.js`, `store.js`, `widget-registry.js`, `config-loader.js`, `event-bus.js`, and `js/widgets/*.js`.

### Widget system
- Widgets are **factory functions** imported in `js/app.js` (`widgetFactories` map).
- Three **active** widget types: `clock`, `notes` (Sticky Notes), `todo` (To-Do).
- Three **dormant** types kept for backward compat: `bookmarks`, `search`, `sysinfo` — must **not** appear in the Add Widget picker.
- Each widget instance requires a **stable unique `id`** and **scoped** localStorage payload — no shared global key across instances.
- Widget shells (title, controls) live in `app.js`/`index.html`, **not** inside widget renderers. Renderers must not duplicate the title.

### localStorage schema
Namespace: `calvybots_*`. Active keys:
- `calvybots_widgets` — widget layout array with embedded per-instance state (`notesState`, `todoState`).
- `calvybots_title` — dashboard site title string.
- `calvybots_bookmarks` — bookmarks array (legacy widget, still migrated).
- `calvybots_user_config` — user config overrides (for `config-loader.js`).

Legacy keys `calvybots_notes` and `calvybots_todo` must be migrated via `migrateLegacyIfNeeded()` in `store.js` on first load — never silently dropped.

### PWA and service worker
- `sw.js` uses **network-first** strategy for same-origin GET requests.
- Precache: `index.html`, `css/style.css`, `js/app.js`, `js/store.js`, widget modules, `manifest.json`, `icons/icon.svg`.
- **`/api/` must never be intercepted or cached** by the service worker.
- Cross-origin CDN requests (Tailwind, Alpine, marked, DOMPurify) are **not** cached — online-first CDN behavior.
- `manifest.json` must be served with `application/manifest+json` MIME type.
- `sw.js` must be served with `Cache-Control: no-store` so the browser always fetches it fresh.

### nginx / backend
- Primary config: `nginx-site.conf`.
- API proxy: `/api/` → `http://api:3000`.
- Static assets get appropriate `Cache-Control` (long TTL for hashed assets, short for `index.html`, `sw.js`, `manifest.json`).
- Security headers must not break PWA install or SW scope.

---

## Visual design rules

### Palette — cyan/dark (v4 direction)
- Page background: `#1c1c1c` (charcoal).
- Surface / cards: `#242424`.
- Elevated controls: `#2e2e2e`.
- Border: `#3d3d3d`.
- **Primary accent: `#2dd4bf` (cyan)** — use for interactive highlights, focus rings, active states.
- Primary text: `#f0f0f0`.
- Secondary text: `#9a9a9a`.
- Muted/metadata: `#5c5c5c`.

**No stray purple in active UI states.** The CSS still has some violet/indigo in `.btn-*` rules — these should be migrated to cyan variants when touched.

### Component patterns
- Widget card (`.dash-widget`): gradient fill, soft border, lift on hover.
- Buttons: dark neutral gradient with border; accent gradient for primary actions.
- Inputs: dark background, high-contrast `:focus-visible` ring.
- Motion cap: **240ms**, `ease-out` only; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Touch targets: minimum **42px** for all interactive controls.

### Typography
- Headline `h1`: `1.5–1.875rem`, `font-weight: 600`.
- Widget title (`.widget-title`): `0.72rem`, `font-weight: 600`, all-caps, tracked.
- Body: `1rem`, `font-weight: 400`, `line-height: 1.45`.
- Caption: `0.75rem`, muted text.

---

## Code quality rules

- **No unsanitized `innerHTML` from user content.** Notes Markdown must pass through DOMPurify (or equivalent safe renderer) before insertion.
- **No duplicate widget titles** — shell renders the title once; widget renderer must not add its own title block.
- **Keyboard accessibility:** all controls reachable via keyboard, visible `:focus-visible` on every interactive element.
- **Icon-only controls** must have `aria-label`.
- **Accessible names** required on all form controls.
- Use `structuredClone` (with JSON fallback) for deep copies — never mutate shared objects.
- `async`/`await` error paths must not silently swallow failures; log with `console.error`.
- Imports use relative paths (`./widgets/clock.js`), not bare specifiers.

---

## Process and documentation rules

- **Source of truth for product direction:** `team/brief.md`, `team/delegation-v4.md`, `team/lead-status.md`.
- **Style tokens source of truth:** `team/style-guide.md` (currently v3; update to v4 when cyan token pass is complete).
- **QA sign-off artifacts:** `team/qa-complete-v4.md`, `team/qa-status.md`, `tests/test-plan.md`, `tests/usability-checklist.md`.
- When introducing new interaction patterns (resize handles, recurrence controls, markdown toolbar), update `team/style-guide.md`.
- Dated architecture amendments go in `team/brief.md` under `## Update YYYY-MM-DD`.
- **No PRs expected for internal dev sprints** (see `team/brief.md §8`); git commits sufficient.
- Team Lead must update `team/lead-status.md` and assignment files after each delegation cycle.

---

## File ownership quick reference

| File / folder | Owner agent |
|---------------|-------------|
| `index.html` | Frontend |
| `css/style.css` | Frontend |
| `js/app.js` | Frontend |
| `js/store.js` | Frontend |
| `js/widgets/*.js` | Frontend |
| `js/config-loader.js` | Frontend / Backend |
| `js/widget-registry.js` | Frontend |
| `js/event-bus.js` | Frontend |
| `sw.js` | Backend |
| `nginx-site.conf`, `nginx.conf` | Backend |
| `manifest.json` | Backend / Frontend (joint) |
| `docker-compose.yml` | Backend |
| `data/config.json`, `data/schema.md` | Backend / Frontend (joint) |
| `team/*.md` | Team Lead (or delegated agent) |
| `tests/*.md` | QA |
| `.cursor/agents/*.md` | Team Lead |
